abstract: I like the 17th but I'm really looking forward to tomorrow's 18th after work. Make it a long one. Montematre is faaaannnnntasticccc. So much to see. 😁

There’s some pretty good shopping on Avenue de Ternes as well— although heavy on the chains— if people are curious. The 17th was the first area I ventured out to in Paris all by myself from the 19th. My ex husband worked there. I have a lot of memories of it there! Also, the Promenade Pereire has those arbors you showed and they EXPLODE with roses in early June! 🌹🌹🌹🌹 It’s very pretty and a great place to take photos, if people are into that! Thanks, Jay. 🙏🏼✌🏼

I stayed in the 17th when I was there last week. It was beautiful. A quiet area away from a lot of touristy stuff, which liked. Great location for us. We stayed at the Art Hotel Batignolles. Great little boutique hotel.
